## Design decisions
- Explicit Bearer beats cookie; invalid Bearer → 401 (no cookie fallthrough)
- Analytics SSE prefers ?token=/Bearer over session cookie
- Terminal stream errors always SSE-framed (`data:` + `[DONE]`) with text/event-stream
- 401/403 advance to next model after in-provider key rotation exhausted
- Per-attempt asyncio.wait_for budget = min(remaining, 120s)

## Lessons
- .cursorrules can be overwritten by concurrent agent sessions — re-read before editing, merge don't clobber
- Spokenly MCP may be unavailable; supercoder says NEVER ASK — proceed autonomously
- Project venv is `.venv` (uv), not `venv`
- EventSource cannot send Authorization — use ?token= or session cookie for SSE
- Empty-stream last-model must continue — fall-through yields HTTP 200
- stream_failed must mutate StreamResult via holder after construction
- Awaiting cancelled Task re-raises CancelledError — catch explicitly
- except BaseException before except Exception makes Exception unreachable
- Broad monkeypatch of asyncio.wait_for also hits per-attempt deadlines — tests must accept request_deadline_exceeded
- Zero-fill must coarsen step or fill from until — capping from since drops newest buckets
